narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I did not gain many skills past what I already knew from Calculus AB in high school.
I developed basic skills needed to solve problems in calculus.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The biggest strength of this course were the Ximera assignments. I learned a lot from that format. The weakness was more so with the class environment not the material itself.
Some PSET problems were unnecessarily difficult and it served no purpose; it just made everything confusing and resulted in the actual concept not being understood.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this course if you struggled with calculus in high school or if you have never taken calculus.

Not really because it was basic calculus but at times was just made complicated for no real reason. For example, some PSET problems were difficult enough that my teacher and peer tutors had trouble with them and that caused many students, myself included, to not really understand the underlying concept.
